# Downloading GitHub Actions Artifacts

When a user shares a GitHub Actions artifact URL, use the convenience script to download logs directly into `pytest_logs/`.

## Usage

```bash
tests/download_ci_logs.sh <artifact_url>
```

**Example:**

```bash
tests/download_ci_logs.sh https://github.com/unifyai/unity/actions/runs/20537719146/artifacts/4974812109
```

This downloads and extracts the artifact directly into `pytest_logs/`, placing CI logs alongside any local test logs.

## URL Format

The script automatically extracts the artifact ID from the URL:

```
https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/actions/runs/{run_id}/artifacts/{artifact_id}
                                            ↑                      ↑
                                         run_id              artifact_id
```

## After Downloading

View the logs using Shell (`ls`) and Read tools (see `gitignored-directory-access.mdc`):

```bash
# List downloaded log directories
ls pytest_logs/

# List files in a specific run
ls pytest_logs/2025-12-27T10-15-40_unitypid3272/
```

Then use the Read tool to inspect specific log files.

## Manual Alternative

If the script isn't available, download directly via the GitHub API:

```bash
gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/actions/artifacts/{artifact_id}/zip > /tmp/artifact.zip && \
  python3 -c "import zipfile; zipfile.ZipFile('/tmp/artifact.zip').extractall('pytest_logs/')"
```
